table-0491-266.caption: Building Layout
data: Barony Bar: A bar where many events in the union are held. The bar contains two large projector screens to facilitate these. The Barony is considered one of the more popular and more frequented bars of the Union.

Gamezone: The Gamezone on the 3rd floor of the Union houses Scotland’s largest pool hall. Also contains a jukebox and several quiz and fruit machines. Have a number of 3D televisions used to televise sports events. Santander Bank: An on campus bank which provides all of the services of a normal high street bank. Shop: Sells a variety of items. These include confectionery, notepads, and University branded items such as hooded-sweatshirts and lab coats.

The Scene: Open daily for breakfast. Serves a variety of food & drink, including vegetarian and halal options. Have several plasma screen televisions which makes it a popular place for students to congregate between lectures.

The Lounge: Home of the Advice Hub support service. Also provides a space where students can carry out a variety of activities including relaxing with friends, reading over lecture notes, and holding meetings.

The Andrew Hamnett Debates Chamber Host’s debates but also shows films, hosts student meetings and hosts meet and greets. Liberation Groups room: Contains a central hub for the Liberation groups and an activities room and a private space dedicated to the Liberation groups where they can work and plan activities. Starbucks @ Priory: Serves Starbucks in newly renovated Priory.
Central Services, Communications and Finance: Where most of the behind the scenes work required to keep the Union running is carried out.
Board Room: Union archives and a few meeting rooms.
